Bins that were identified in the merged profile database 'Psonoriensis 1F' and stored in the database as "maxbin2" collection, describe 87 bins accountig for 291,843,175 nucleotides, which represent 34.41% of all nucleotides stored in the contigs database, and 34.44% of nucleotides stored in the profile database.

Basics

The merged profile database that was generated with the minimum contig length of 1,000 contained 21,637 contigs, which correspond to 93% of all contigs, and 99% of all nucleotides found in the contigs database.

Percent Recruitment

This panel shows how much of the mapped data is recruited by each bin (and how much of the mapped data was not binned under 'splits_not_binned' column). The way these percents calculated is quite simple: summarize the mean coverage of each split in each bin, and normalize every bin with respect to each other. It is critical to remember that these values do not take the unasssambled data into account. This is how you should read this table: "X percent of all mapped reads in Sample Y mapped to splits that were binned into bin Z".
